@Node Einleitung "GuideML: Introduction"

@{B} I N T R O D U C T I O N @{UB}
__________________________________________________________________________
@{FG SHINE}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{FG TEXT}

Uuuh... Yet Another (tm) AmigaGuide to HTML converter?

Yes. You are right. But...

I wrote GuideML just because the other converters were @{I}much@{UI} too
slow (compiled ARexx, you know) and had really worse limitations. Did
you ever try to feed a TexInfo based AmigaGuide into these converters?

And this is the result: the ultimate AmigaGuide to HTML converter!

I hope it is as useful to you as it is to me. If you have some questions,
suggestions, whatever, feel free to write @{" me " link Adresse} !

                                                Richard Körber

@EndNode
@Node Features "GuideML: Features"

@{B} F E A T U R E S @{UB}
__________________________________________________________________________
@{FG SHINE}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{FG TEXT}

This are the features of GuideML:

· Converts any AmigaGuide compliant documentation into a multi-file
  HTML 3.2 document.

· Converts all non-ASCII characters into the appropriate HTML entities.
  The result is a 100% clean HTML document, viewable on @{B}all@{UB} systems
  with @{B}all@{UB} browsers (even text based ones).

· Fully supports \@next, \@prev, \@toc, \@index and \@help commands.
  Hierarchial table of contents are also supported.

· Supports font style (\@{B},...) and color (\@{FG ...}) commands. \@{BG}
  is not supported due to HTML 3.2 limitations.

· Navigation bar with "CONTENTS", "INDEX", "NEXT", "PREV", "HELP", "RETRACE"
  and "HOME" button. (Also as footer if you like!)

· Navigation titles freely changeable. You can also insert images.
  (A free set of images is automatically saved upon request.)

· Automatically detects Internet links (http:, ftp:, mailto:, ...) and
  creates an <a href> link for them. E-Mail addresses are also detected.

· @{"Sourcecode" link Source} included under GNU public licence

There are some restrictions if you want to use the result on other
operating systems (MS-DOS or UN*X):

· Don't use Umlauts (non-ASCII chars like Ä,Ö,Ü) in Node names if you
  want to get UN*X compilant file names.

· MS-DOS styled filenames are not supported if you didn't. They are
  simply too short! :-) GuideML only supports the .htm ending using the
  MSDOS parameter.

@EndNode
